  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kabul.LGA.Understanding and Policies of Islamist Insurgencies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Humanitarian Policy Group (HPG) at the Overseas Development Institute (ODI) are commissioning a two-year research project to improve understandings of how Islamist armed non state groups (ANSAs) govern territories that they control, and what factors influence this. The aim of this research is to provide pragmatic, policy-relevant recommendations for engagement. The project will forge strong links with aid groups on the ground, the broader field of researchers and academics working on insurgent governance, as well as policy makers and donors. It will directly contribute to the practice of aid work in volatile environments as well as the growing focus on working and thinking politically, and on the ways in which understanding localised political settlements is essential to working effectively in fragile contexts.</narrative>
  </description>
